<h3>Challenges</h3>
<p>To begin this animation process, the provided artwork required further manipulation in Illustrator. Each orb signal was recreated as a path in order to function correctly with <a href="https://greensock.com/drawSVG">DrawSVG</a>. The other challenging aspects were to create two instances of frames for the breathing sequence. To construct this morphing effect two states had to be created; one for the mouth and one for chest. Each of these states were hand manipulated in illustrator using the b√©zier anchor tool to pull the shapes anchor points into position. The pulsating orb behind the child also had to be recreated from scratch in Illustrator and sized appropriately.</p>
<p>The entire motion sequence required some considerable critical thinking in order to stage it perfectly. Timing was achieved using a series of calculated and placed callback methods in JavaScript that would determine and report when each orb was to emit a wave to the child's brain. Proper naming conventions and organization of layers in Illustrator helped to facilitate this process making the animation work effecient in regards to coding purposes.</p>

